properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS -  Wollongong Education Precinct - WOLLONGONG Princes Motorway, Memorial Drive at University of Wollongong
properties.adviceB: Use diversions; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Traffic management will be in place around University of Wollongong during morning peak periods to help ease congestion and queuing on the M1 Princes Motorway.

From 7:45am to 9:15am Monday to Friday:

  • M1 Princes Mwy southbound traffic exiting at University Ave will be diverted left to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout.
  • Traffic at Irvine St will diverted left, to the University Western Access route.
  • Motorists wishing to access the M1 Princes Mwy northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Ave will be diverted via Murphys Ave and Robsons Rd.

Motorists should allow extra travel time during morning peak and follow instructions of traffic controllers.

properties.publicTransport:
Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip on public transport.
Some buses are diverted and delayed in the Raymond Terrace to Newcastle area.
properties.otherAdvice:
Northbound motorists heading towards Hexham can use M1 Pacific Mwy, Newcastle Link Rd, Newcastle Inner City Bypass and Maitland Rd, however traffic is extremely heavy.

Northbound motorists heading to Raymond Terrace and beyond can use M1 Pacific Mwy, Weakleys Dr, Glenwood Dr, Thornton Rd/Railway Ave/Edwards Ave/Government Rd, Raymond Terrace Rd, William Bailey St and Adelaide St to join the Pacific Hwy.Southbound/westbound motorists should consider using Maitland Rd, Newcastle Inner City Bypass, Newcastle Link Rd and the M1 Pacific Mwy to travel between Hexham and Newcastle Interchange/Beresfield.

Southbound/westbound should consider using Maitland Rd, Newcastle Inner City Bypass, Newcastle Link Rd and the M1 Pacific Mwy to travel between Hexham and Newcastle Interchange.
